{
  "text": "The strains and plasmids used in this study are listed in Table 1 . Expression of bdcA was induced by 0.1 mM isopropyl-\u03b2-D-thiogalactopyranoside (IPTG) (Sigma, St. Louis, MO). Luria-Bertani (LB) [CITATION_1] was used for all the experiments. Chloramphenicol (50 \u03bcg/mL for R. meliloti and 250 \u03bcg/mL for Pseudomonas sp.) was used for strains harboring pMMB206 and pMMB206-BdcA. Carbenicillin (50 \u03bcg/mL) was used for strains harboring pP25-gfp. 37\u00b0C was used for all P. aeruginosa tests, and 30\u00b0C was used for P. fluorescens and R. meliloti tests.",
